Eragrostis superba

   [5745.jpg]
    Authority   Peyr.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms   Eragrostis superba var. contracta Peter
   Common names sawtooth lovegrass, weeluis eragrostis
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5745

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A densely tufted grass, 30-90 cm high. USES Used for
   pasture, stands should not be grazed until the second summer after
   seeding. In a mixed pasture it may be grazed out. Near maturity the
   stems get unpalatable and its nutritive value drops. GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial grass, with a economical life of 2-4 years. COMMON NAMES
   Masai love grass, Heart-seed love grass, Flat-seed love grass, Wilman
   love grass. FURTHER INF Scientific synonyms: E. elata, E. platystachys,
   Uniola jardinii. Masai love grass is native of southern and tropical
   Africa. It can be found at elevations between sea level and 2000 m and
   is common in open thicket and grasslend on poor sandy soils, often as a
   weed. Dry matter yields are usually between 3-6 t/ha, but yields of up
   to 24 t/ha have been recorded.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Skerman P 1990 pp 425-427 [LIG, TEXT, LIMIT, KTMP, RAIN, DRA, PH, SAL]
   Bogdan A 1977 pp 140-141 [RAIN, TEXT, LIG, DRA, DEP]
   IBPGR 1984 pp 183

